Surface and vestiture.
Dorsum shiny, head smooth, pronotum with dense deep punctures (
Figs 15–16
), hemelytron weakly rugose. Entire body with long, erect to semierect pale simple setae; femoral trichobothria deeply recessed and tuberculate (
Figs 20–21
); tibial spines absent; appendages with short, semierect to adpressed pale simple setae.
